A Resolution recognizing February 26, 2025, as
9 Hypertrophic Cardiomyopathy Awareness Day at the
State Capitol; and expressing the importance of
10 Hypertrophic Cardiomyopathy Awareness Day.
11
12
13 WHEREAS, hypertrophic cardiomyopathy (HCM) is a chronic cardiac
14 disease involving thickening of the heart muscle and can potentially
15 lead to debilitating symptoms and serious complications including
16 heart failure, atrial fibrillation, stroke, and in rare cases sudden
17 cardiac death; and
18 WHEREAS, HCM is the most common inheritable heart disease and
19 can affect anyone regardless of age, gender, or ethnicity with a
20 reported prevalence ranging from 1 in 200 to 1 in 500 in the general
21 population; and
22 WHEREAS, an estimated 700,000 to 1,650,000 people in the United
23 States have HCM, yet 85% of them may remain undiagnosed; and
