1 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
2 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
3 THAT the fourth Wednesday, February 26, 2025, is hereby
4 recognized by the Oklahoma House of Representatives and the State of
5 Oklahoma as Hypertrophic Cardiomyopathy Awareness Day, in order to
6 raise public awareness about hypertrophic cardiomyopathy.
7 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives acknowledges the
8 critical importance of hypertrophic cardiomyopathy awareness to
9 improve cardiovascular health in the State of Oklahoma.
10 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives supports raising
11 awareness of the consequences of undiagnosed and untreated
12 hypertrophic cardiomyopathy and the need to seek appropriate care
13 for hypertrophic cardiomyopathy as a serious public health issue.
